Citation.sAbstract: Using the laser monitoring observation technique, the solubilities of dimethyl fumarate in methanol, ethanol, 1-propanol, 2-propanol, 1,2-propanediol, and water have been determined experimentally from (289.95 to 347.15) K. The experimental data were correlated with the modified Apelblat equation. The calculated results showed good agreement with the experimental data.
Citation.sTitle: Solubility of Dimethyl Fumarate in Methanol, Ethanol, 1-Propanol, 2-Propanol, 1,2-Propanediol, and Water from (289.95 to 347.15) K
